{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Libya", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Libya}}\n{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Libya\n| map1            = \n| legend1         = \n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Libya]]\n| first_case      = [[Tripoli]]\n| arrival_date    = 24 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=24|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[China]] \n| recovery_cases  = 1\n| deaths          = 1\n| confirmed_cases = 20<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/#countries |title=Coronavirus Update (Live): 1,341,662 Cases and 74,522 Deaths from COVID-19 Virus Outbreak - Worldometer |website=www.worldometers.info |language=en |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = \n}}\nThis article is about the spread of the [[coronavirus]] in [[Libya]], during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2020 epidemic]].\n\nLibya is considered especially vulnerable to the epidemic due to the ongoing [[Libyan Civil War]], which has led to a dire humanitarian situation<ref name=first/> and a destruction of the nation's health infrastructure.<ref name=RocketAttack>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/condemns-rocket-attack-tripoli-hospital-200407140610239.html UN condemns rocket attack on Tripoli hospital], Al Jazeera (April 7, 2020).</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, who had initially come to the attention of the WHO on 31 December 2019. This cluster was initially linked to the [[Huanan Seafood Wholesale Market]] in Wuhan City. However, some of those first cases with laboratory confirmed results had no link to the market, and the source of the epidemic is unknown.<ref name=\"Elsevier\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center|last=Elsevier|date=|website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Reynolds4March2020\">{{Cite news|last=Reynolds|first=Matt|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic?|date=4 March 2020|work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|issn=1357-0978}}</ref>\n\nUnlike [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]], the [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 <ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus|website=Imperial News|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England|last=|first=|date=|website=GOV.UK|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> has been much lower, but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=\"WFSA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" /> COVID-19 typically appears with about seven days of [[Influenza-like illness|flu-like symptoms]] followed by some people progressing to symptoms of a [[viral pneumonia]] requiring admission to hospital.<ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" /> From 19 March, COVID-19 was no longer classified as a \"High consequence infectious disease\".<ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\" />\n\n==Timeline==\n===March 2020===\nPrior to the coronavirus pandemic, Libya's healthcare system was already on the verge of collapse, given the chaos that has prevailed in the country [[Libyan Civil War (2011)|since 2011]].<ref name=450Prisoners>[Lhttps://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/libya-frees-450-prisoners-stem-spread-coronavirus-200330093545745.html ibya frees more than 450 prisoners to stem spread of coronavirus], Al Jazeera (March 30, 2020).</ref> Warring factions in the [[Libyan Civil War]] disregarded repeated entreaties from the [[United Nations]] for a ceasefire during the pandemic.<ref name=RocketAttack/><ref name=Humanitarian>[https://reliefweb.int/report/libya/statement-humanitarian-coordinator-libya-yacoub-el-hillo-following-today-s-attack-al Statement by the Humanitarian Coordinator for Libya, Yacoub El Hillo, following today's attack on Al Khadra General Hospital in Tripoli], United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (April 6, 2020).</ref>\n\nThe internationally recognized [[Government of National Accord]] (GNA), based in Tripoli, and the rival government under [[Khalifa Haftar]], based in eastern Libya, both took steps to control the spread of COVID-19, through the closure of schools, markets, and some businesses.<ref name=450Prisoners/> Haftar's forces have attempted to take Tripoli, the Libyan capital, in an offensive that began in April 2019.<ref name=450Prisoners/> Hundreds have been killed, and thousands have been [[Internally displaced person|displaced]], in the fighting.<ref name=450Prisoners/>\n\nOn 24 March, Libya confirmed its first [[COVID-19]] case,<ref name=first>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-libya-measures/libya-confirms-first-coronavirus-case-amid-fear-over-readiness-idUSKBN21B2SF|title=Libya confirms first coronavirus case amid fear over readiness|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=24 March 2020|access-date=24 March 2020}}</ref> a 73-year-old man who had returned to the country in early March from a trip to [[Saudi Arabia]].<ref name=450Prisoners/>\n\nOn March 30, the GNA announced the release of 466 detainees in Tripoli, as part of an effort to stop the spread of the virus in prisons.<ref name=450Prisoners/>\n\n===April 2020===\nOn 2 April, Libya confirmed its first COVID-19 death. It was an 85-year-old Algerian woman.\n\nOn April 5, [[Mahmoud Jibril]], age 68, who headed the interim [[National Transitional Council]] in 2011, died from COVID-19 in [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]], having been admitted to the hospital on March 21.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/libya-prime-minister-mahmoud-jibril-dies-coronavirus-200405162834328.html Former Libya Prime Minister Mahmoud Jibril dies from coronavirus], Al Jazeera (April 5, 2020).</ref>\n\nBy April 7, Libya had confirmed 20 cases of COVID-19, mostly in western Libya.<ref name=APTripoli/> \n\nOn April 6, Forces under the command of [[Khalifa Haftar]] launched a [[BM-21 Grad|Grad rocket]] attack<ref name=APTripoli>[https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2020/04/07/world/middleeast/ap-ml-libya-.html Eastern Libyan Forces Attack Tripoli Hospital for Second Day], Associated Press (April 7, 2020).</ref> against Al Khadra General Hospital, one of Tripoli's largest hospitals, injured six health workers and substantially damaged the hospital,<ref name=RocketAttack/> where 300 patients, including two COVID-19 patients, were being treated.<ref name=APTripoli/> This was the third time that Haftar's forces attacked medical facilities during their intensified siege of Tripoli.<ref name=APTripoli/> The [[United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs]] condemned the attack as an \"appalling\" and \"clear violation of [[international humanitarian law]] ... It is unacceptable at a time when healthcare and health workers are vital in our fight against a global pandemic.\"<ref name=RocketAttack/> The office stated that \"This senseless escalation must stop so that health authorities and aid agencies can respond to COVID-19 and continue reaching people in need of urgent humanitarian assistance.\"<ref name=Humanitarian/> Renewed rocket attacks against the hospital continued the following day.<ref name=APTripoli/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Libya|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Libya]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Africa|Libya]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Libya]]\n\n\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n{{Libya-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Libya}}\n{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Libya\n| map1            = \n| legend1         = \n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Libya]]\n| first_case      = [[Tripoli]]\n| arrival_date    = 24 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=24|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[China]] \n| recovery_cases  = 1\n| deaths          = 1\n| confirmed_cases = 20<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/#countries |title=Coronavirus Update (Live): 1,341,662 Cases and 74,522 Deaths from COVID-19 Virus Outbreak - Worldometer |website=www.worldometers.info |language=en |access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = \n}}\nThis article is about the spread of the [[coronavirus]] in [[Libya]], during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2020 epidemic]].\n\nLibya is considered especially vulnerable to the epidemic due to the ongoing [[Libyan Civil War]], which has led to a dire humanitarian situation<ref name=first/> and a destruction of the nation's health infrastructure.<ref name=RocketAttack>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/condemns-rocket-attack-tripoli-hospital-200407140610239.html UN condemns rocket attack on Tripoli hospital], Al Jazeera (April 7, 2020).</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, who had initially come to the attention of the WHO on 31 December 2019. This cluster was initially linked to the [[Huanan Seafood Wholesale Market]] in Wuhan City. However, some of those first cases with laboratory confirmed results had no link to the market, and the source of the epidemic is unknown.<ref name=\"Elsevier\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center|last=Elsevier|date=|website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Reynolds4March2020\">{{Cite news|last=Reynolds|first=Matt|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic?|date=4 March 2020|work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|issn=1357-0978}}</ref>\n\nUnlike [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]], the [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 <ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus|website=Imperial News|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England|last=|first=|date=|website=GOV.UK|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> has been much lower, but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=\"WFSA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" /> COVID-19 typically appears with about seven days of [[Influenza-like illness|flu-like symptoms]] followed by some people progressing to symptoms of a [[viral pneumonia]] requiring admission to hospital.<ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" /> From 19 March, COVID-19 was no longer classified as a \"High consequence infectious disease\".<ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\" />\n\n==Timeline==\n===March 2020===\nPrior to the coronavirus pandemic, Libya's healthcare system was already on the verge of collapse, given the chaos that has prevailed in the country [[Libyan Civil War (2011)|since 2011]].<ref name=450Prisoners>[Lhttps://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/libya-frees-450-prisoners-stem-spread-coronavirus-200330093545745.html ibya frees more than 450 prisoners to stem spread of coronavirus], Al Jazeera (March 30, 2020).</ref> Warring factions in the [[Libyan Civil War]] disregarded repeated entreaties from the [[United Nations]] for a ceasefire during the pandemic.<ref name=RocketAttack/><ref name=Humanitarian>[https://reliefweb.int/report/libya/statement-humanitarian-coordinator-libya-yacoub-el-hillo-following-today-s-attack-al Statement by the Humanitarian Coordinator for Libya, Yacoub El Hillo, following today's attack on Al Khadra General Hospital in Tripoli], United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (April 6, 2020).</ref>\n\nThe internationally recognized [[Government of National Accord]] (GNA), based in Tripoli, and the rival government under [[Khalifa Haftar]], based in eastern Libya, both took steps to control the spread of COVID-19, through the closure of schools, markets, and some businesses.<ref name=450Prisoners/> Haftar's forces have attempted to take Tripoli, the Libyan capital, in an offensive that began in April 2019.<ref name=450Prisoners/> Hundreds have been killed, and thousands have been [[Internally displaced person|displaced]], in the fighting.<ref name=450Prisoners/>\n\nOn 24 March, Libya confirmed its first [[COVID-19]] case,<ref name=first>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-libya-measures/libya-confirms-first-coronavirus-case-amid-fear-over-readiness-idUSKBN21B2SF|title=Libya confirms first coronavirus case amid fear over readiness|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=24 March 2020|access-date=24 March 2020}}</ref> a 73-year-old man who had returned to the country in early March from a trip to [[Saudi Arabia]].<ref name=450Prisoners/>\n\nOn March 30, the GNA announced the release of 466 detainees from prisons in Tripoli, as part of an effort to stop the spread of the virus among detained persons.<ref name=450Prisoners/>\n\n===April 2020===\nOn 2 April, Libya confirmed its first COVID-19 death. It was an 85-year-old Algerian woman.\n\nOn April 5, [[Mahmoud Jibril]], age 68, who headed the interim [[National Transitional Council]] in 2011, died from COVID-19 in [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]], having been admitted to the hospital on March 21.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/libya-prime-minister-mahmoud-jibril-dies-coronavirus-200405162834328.html Former Libya Prime Minister Mahmoud Jibril dies from coronavirus], Al Jazeera (April 5, 2020).</ref>\n\nBy April 7, Libya had confirmed 20 cases of COVID-19, mostly in western Libya.<ref name=APTripoli/> \n\nOn April 6, Forces under the command of [[Khalifa Haftar]] launched a [[BM-21 Grad|Grad rocket]] attack<ref name=APTripoli>[https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2020/04/07/world/middleeast/ap-ml-libya-.html Eastern Libyan Forces Attack Tripoli Hospital for Second Day], Associated Press (April 7, 2020).</ref> against Al Khadra General Hospital, one of Tripoli's largest hospitals, injured six health workers and substantially damaged the hospital,<ref name=RocketAttack/> where 300 patients, including two COVID-19 patients, were being treated.<ref name=APTripoli/> This was the third time that Haftar's forces attacked medical facilities during their intensified siege of Tripoli.<ref name=APTripoli/> The [[United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs]] condemned the attack as an \"appalling\" and \"clear violation of [[international humanitarian law]] ... It is unacceptable at a time when healthcare and health workers are vital in our fight against a global pandemic.\"<ref name=RocketAttack/> The office stated that \"This senseless escalation must stop so that health authorities and aid agencies can respond to COVID-19 and continue reaching people in need of urgent humanitarian assistance.\"<ref name=Humanitarian/> Renewed rocket attacks against the hospital continued the following day.<ref name=APTripoli/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Libya|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Libya]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Africa|Libya]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Libya]]\n\n\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n{{Libya-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Neutrality", "label": "safe", "comment": "simplify", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Libya"}
